### Mule Pack Transport Company


Though not directly partaking in frontline combat, the Cyprus Regiment provided essential equipment, food and much needed support in the many theatres of war. A total of six Mule Pack Transport Companies were formed and saw action in:
France,  Dunkirk, East Africa Eritrea, Sudan, Ethiopia
Middle East  Syria against Vichy France
North Africa  Egypt
Greece  Crete
Italy/Sicily  Cassino.

These covers are very difficult to find as the Regiment consisted only about 600 volunteers. (I actually only seen these ones but I am sure there are a few around).
Two of my uncles served in the War, the one got killed in Italy and the other survived the War married an English woman and eventually emigrated to Australia.

